\n\n\n<p><strong>Infosys is at the forefront of this digital revolution. With a global presence and a reputation for excellence<\/strong>, Infosys has become a sought-after destination for talented individuals seeking to embark on a rewarding career journey. However, securing a position at this esteemed organization demands more than just technical proficiency. It requires a well-rounded approach, combining academic excellence with practical skills, problem-solving abilities, and a deep understanding of the industry&#8217;s dynamics. This blog is about Infosys preparation tips and added five Infosys exam preparation Tips.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Preparing for the Infosys recruitment process is a challenging yet rewarding endeavor, that demands dedication, perseverance, and a strategic mindset. By following a structured and focused approach, aspiring candidates can unlock the doors to a future brimming with opportunities for growth and professionalism.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"infosys-exam-preparation-tips-for-2024\">Infosys Exam Preparation Tips for 2024<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The 5 Preparation tips for the Infosys Examination are added here. Graduates can check out the Infosys Exam Preparation Tip below:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"1-understand-the-question-paper-structure\">1. Understand the Question Paper Structure<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The online test lasts for 1 hour 45 minutes. It consists of sections, such as verbal, pseudo-code, and technical sections. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Infosys Exam Pattern<\/strong><\/td><td><strong>No of Questions <\/strong><\/td><td><strong>Total Time <\/strong><\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Mathematical Ability<\/td><td>10 Questions <\/td><td>35 Mins<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Logic<\/td><td>15 Questions<\/td><td>25 Mins<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Verbal Ability<\/td><td>20 Questions <\/td><td>20 Mins<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Puzzle Solving<\/td><td>4Questions<\/td><td>10 Mins<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Pseudo Code<\/td><td>5 Questions<\/td><td>10 Mins <\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Total <\/td><td>54 Questions <\/td><td>100 Mins ( 1hr 40 mins )<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>There is a sectional cut-off, but no negative marking for incorrect answers. You must complete one section at a time and cannot switch between sections. Your answers are automatically saved once the time for each section is up. If you complete a section before the allotted time, go to the next section. Attempt all questions, and for any unsolved or unknown questions, choose the same answer option consistently.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"2-practice-with-the-infosys-mock-test-2024-by-skillvertex\">2. Practice with the Infosys Mock Test 2024 By Skillvertex<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Applicants can solve the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/infosys-mock-test\/\">Infosys Mock Test<\/a> provided by Skillvertex. Regularly Practicing this mock test &#8211; will help you to know the Infosys exam pattern and understand the marking scheme for the examination. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The mock test series by Skillvertex is one of the best Mock tests, prepared by various experts, and will provide instant feedback with the solution. You will get an instant solution with a detailed explanation after the test.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Furthermore, this mock test will prepare you well for the Infosys Examination. It will improve your skills and knowledge about various sections of the Infosys examination. Those sections include Pseudo Code, Numerical Ability and Puzzle Solving<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"3-solve-infosys-previous-year-paper\">3. Solve Infosys Previous Year Paper<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Solving <a href=\"http:\/\/Infosys Previous Year Paper-Download PDF With Answers\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">previous year&#8217;s papers<\/a> is crucial for your preparation. Start by understanding the exam pattern, section-wise weightage, and question types. Analyze your strong and weak areas from the previous year&#8217;s papers. For difficult questions, read the explanations thoroughly to grasp the concepts.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Practice similar questions repeatedly until you are confident. Time management is key &#8211; refer to the sectional time limits and practice accordingly.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p> Additionally, take mock tests to simulate the real exam environment and improve your speed and accuracy. Consistently practicing previous year&#8217;s papers will boost your confidence and help you identify your blind spots to work on.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"4-start-with-easy-questions-first\">4. Start with  Easy Questions First<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Some questions are challenging and require deep understanding, while others are easier to solve with practice. Within the first 15 minutes, focus on attempting 6 less time-consuming questions, including 3 to 4 easy ones that can be solved quickly. Then, spend more time on the remaining 4 questions.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p> The goal is to get at least 6 to 7 correct answers to meet the expected cut-off. The most crucial part is identifying the 6 less time-consuming questions and solving them first.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Graduates can begin with questions that can be solved quickly. Get through 9 of those in 15 minutes. Then do the Data Interpretation questions that use charts\/tables. Leave the Data Arrangement questions until the end since they are more time-consuming.  You can get 10-11 questions right overall, you can meet the cut-off requirement.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"5-try-the-error-spotting-or-sentence-correction-next\">5. Try the Error Spotting or Sentence Correction Next<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Start with the easier questions like Sentence Correction, Error Spotting, and Vocabulary. Then, move to Reading Comprehension, tackling longer passages first but not spending too much time understanding every detail. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Answer the straightforward questions based on the passage within 5 minutes, and make guesses for the remaining questions.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally, attempt 5-6 Critical Reasoning questions within 10 minutes. The goal is to get at least 20 correct answers to meet the expected cut-off score. Remember, there&#8217;s no negative marking, so it&#8217;s better to attempt all questions instead of leaving any blank.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"important-things-to-remember-for-infosys-exam-preparation\"> Important Things to Remember for Infosys Exam Preparation<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Infosys generally has a 65% cut-off mark for any test during training programs.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>For the recruitment test, you can expect a similar 65% cut-off for Sections I and II.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>However, the actual cut-off mark for your college or university is different. <\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Infosys decides this cut-off based on a few factors:<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>How well did students from your college\/university perform in the past when they got selected at Infosys?<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>How the alumni (former students) from your college\/university are currently performing at Infosys.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>The percentage of students from your college\/university who left Infosys after completing the training.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>The percentage of students from your college\/university who left Infosys within one<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Preparing for the Infosys exam requires a well-rounded approach. Start by strengthening your programming concepts, data structures, and algorithms. Solve coding problems with the  Infosys Mock test by Skillvertex. Brush up on your aptitude skills, including quantitative ability, logical reasoning, and verbal ability, by solving previous year&#8217;s question papers.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Time management is crucial during the exam, so practice with mock tests to improve your speed and accuracy. Yourself with SQL and database concepts, as they are frequently tested. For the technical rounds, stay updated on the latest industry trends and Infosys-specific news.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, you should focus on communication skills and practice mock interviews to prepare for the HR rounds. Maintain a positive attitude, get adequate rest, and stay focused throughout your preparation journey.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Consistent practice, dedication, and a strategic approach are key to cracking the Infosys exam. With the right mindset and preparation, you can increase your chances of securing a coveted position at this esteemed organization.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"important-links-infosys-exam-preparation\">Important Links &#8211; Infosys Exam Preparation<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/infosys-exam\/\">Infosys Hiring 2024- Infosys Exam Date, Eligibility Criteria, Exam Pattern<\/a><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/infosys-coding-questions\/\" data-type=\"post\" data-id=\"10880\">Top  Infosys Coding Questions and Answers 2024<\/a><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/infosys-previous-year-paper\/\" data-type=\"post\" data-id=\"10759\">Infosys Previous Year Paper With Answers -Download PDF<\/a><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/infosys-interview-questions\/\" data-type=\"post\" data-id=\"10983\">Top Infosys Interview Questions and Answers For 2024<\/a><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/infosys-exam-syllabus\/\">Infosys Exam Syllabus and Exam Pattern 2024 \u2013 PDF Download<\/a><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/infosys-application-form\/\">Infosys Application Form 2024-Apply Now, Application Link<\/a><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/infosys-eligibility-criteria\/\">Infosys Eligibility Criteria For Freshers And Experienced 2024<\/a><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><